            adept: `Rifts can be any size from microscopic needle-points to portal-sized gateways large enough for vehicles or small structures, with durations extending to hours. The device can access any known dimension within several layers of the mage's home reality, targeting destinations across dimensional boundaries with the same precision as spatial teleportation within normal space.

Pocket dimension creation enters the spell's capabilities. The mage can carve out a stable, self-contained reality bubble roughly the size of a large room, anchored to a fixed location or to the mage's personal dimensional signature. This pocket serves as secure storage, a private meeting space, or a safe room that exists outside normal space. Physical laws within the pocket can be minimally adjusted—light levels, temperature, gravity direction—but cannot be radically redefined.

The device can perceive all dimensional activity within several hundred meters, track extra-dimensional entities moving through hidden layers, and manipulate existing rifts created by others—stabilizing allies' portals, redirecting enemies' dimensional escapes, or forcibly collapsing dimensional attacks before they fully manifest.`,

            expert: `Rift diameter can reach tens of meters, spanning city-block scale, with durations extending to days. The device accesses dimensions several layers deep, including major elemental planes, established pocket realms, and stable parallel timelines closely adjacent to the mage's home reality. Multiple permanent dimensional gateways can be established between fixed locations.

Multiple pocket dimensions can be maintained simultaneously, each up to the size of a small building, with customized environmental parameters. The mage can fold themselves partially into an adjacent dimension, becoming intangible to attacks in normal space while still able to observe and cast spells outward—a powerful defensive technique with significant mana cost. Offensively, rifts can be opened inside targets to banish opponents to hostile near-dimensions.

The device provides full dimensional surveillance of the mage's operational theater, tracking all rift activity, extra-dimensional entities, and spatial anomalies. The mage can forcibly seal dimensional breaches caused by others and create dimensional "dead zones" where rift magic cannot function.`,

            master: `The spell operates at its design ceiling. Rifts of any practical size can be opened and maintained with optimized efficiency. The device manages all dimensional calculations in the background, and the mage perceives dimensional topography as a natural extension of spatial awareness. Permanent portal networks, pocket dimensions, dimensional intangibility, and banishment all function at maximum reliability.

The mage can maintain roughly five stable pocket dimensions simultaneously and operate a network of up to a dozen permanent dimensional gateways. Extra-dimensional entities are automatically detected when they enter the mage's awareness range, and the device can preemptively seal dimensional weak points before they become breaches.

This is the ceiling of Dimensional Rift as a Tier 1 spell. The mage is not a multiversal architect who "creates and destroys universes" or "accesses all dimensions across the multiverse simultaneously." What Master provides is the ultimate refinement of a Tier 1 dimensional manipulation spell: access to near-dimensions, stable pocket realms the size of buildings, portal networks, and dimensional defense—a complete toolkit for operating within the dimensional layers immediately adjacent to normal reality.`
