            expert: `Regional mana manipulation: the device taps ley lines beneath entire districts, channeling environmental magic into the mage's reserves at rates that make personal mana effectively unlimited for short periods. Magical phenomena—natural mana storms, ritual bleed-off, dimensional energy leakage—can be harvested. The mage can redistribute magical energy across an operational theater, draining mana from hostile territory and channeling it to allied positions. Artificial ley lines can be created by establishing permanent mana conduits between fixed locations, creating magical infrastructure that persists indefinitely. At this level, the mage is a magical engineer at infrastructure scale.`,

            master: `The spell runs at its design ceiling. Regional mana management across the mage's operational theater operates as an automatic background function—ley line tapping, energy redistribution, and team-pool management all handled without conscious input. Permanent mana wells and artificial ley lines are established and maintained with routine oversight. Energy conversion supports any form the device's computational models can translate. The mage's effective mana reserves during sustained operations far exceed what their reactor rank would normally permit, thanks to continuous environmental harvesting. This is the ceiling of Mana Transfer as a Tier 2 spell: logistical-scale magical energy management—not 'infinite mana' or 'control of all magical energy everywhere.'`
